LAN stands for local area network:-
  -LAN is Private ownership has control over the local area network. such as colleges, schools, hospitals, and so on. 
  -The transmission speed of a LAN is high.

MAN stands for metropolitan area network:-
  -It covers a larger area than LAN such as small towns, cities, etc.
  -While the transmission speed of a MAN is average.

WAN stands for wide area network:-
  -It covers a large area than LAN as well as a MAN such as country/continent etc. 
  -Whereas the transmission speed of a WAN is low.
